comments:
Abolished 1.4.1935 and divided between the parishes of Glenfields 
    and Anstey. See also Table 2, note (g).

Abolished 1.4.1935 and divided between the parishes of Leicester, 
    Thucaston and Beaumont Leys.

On 31.10.1891 most of the parish of Belgrave became part of Leicester 
    County Borough and this area was transferred to Leicester registration district 
    on 1.1.1892. The rural part of Belgrave remaining in Billesdon registration 
    district became part of the parish of Beaumont Leys on 26.3.1892. See also Table 
    2, note (e).

    Linford, Anstey and Ulverscroft.

    and Glenfields. See also Table 2, note (g).
